#29800
{GREEN}Path of the Ferns{green}~

    From out of nowhere a springy path jumps into sight. It
is full of a vibrant green fern-like plants and this gives
it the springy feel that is so comforting. Both sides of 
the path are lined by thick impenetrable trees that climb
far above almost seeming to challenge the darkening sky. 
The land here is green yet the taint of winter is arriving 
with autumn and the cold fingers of snow will soon embrace
all. Peering upwards and through the thick limbs you 
notice small flakes of white...flurries. It appears the
season of ice may be early.

