#29801
{GREEN}Before the FernHouse{green}~

    The pathway continues northward for many hours and its
once beauty has become nothing more than a monotonous 
bore. The ferns are less trampled here from sparse foot
traffic and the giant trees seem almost an ugly scar. 
Their trunks have darkened and seem to writhe as they
twist at unimaginable angles. Knotholes cover their bark
and appear like eyes of a haunted soul. Leaves are thick
with rot and the smell forces you to gag continuously...
this is an ominous warning. Such signs are blatant and you
are unsure whether to continue, but shortly ahead you see
an abandoned tower. It is squat and crumbling yet you
continue onward, answers could be found.

