#29802
{GREEN}Garrison Fern Tower{green}~

    Walking up to the tower forces a gasp of surprise. 
What you believed to be bricks and mortar are nothing 
more than thick tower fronds growing from a huge fern
giving the illusion of a tower. But you were right in 
one aspect for the tower is crumbling. Rotted chunks of
its green leaves are piled at its base, mute evidence 
that this place will likely fall to the elements in a 
short time. Pushing aside a couple fronds you squeeze 
into the interior and mumble ungraciously. Empty but for
a few wooden spears leaning against a far "wall" and a 
round chunk of stone on the dirt floor. There are no 
footprints and the spears appear brittle as a dried 
bramble but the stone is warm to your touch. Perhaps 
the stone may mean something.

